description: It comes after early data showed it protects more than 90% of people from developing Covid symptoms.
title: Coronavirus: EU buys 300m doses of BioNTech-Pfizer vaccine
title_page: Coronavirus: EU buys 300m doses of BioNTech-Pfizer vaccine - BBC News
maintext: But Ms Kyriakides refused to detail a specific timeline for when the vaccine would be delivered to member states. "It has to receive authorisation from the European Medicines Agency," she said. "A number of steps need to be followed before we will actually be able to have a timeline."
